Following up an another discussion regarding `_.range` (https://github.com/lodash/lodash/issues/1539). I think it would be worth adding documentation regarding `_.random` limits if they cause the calculation to exceed max or min safe integer. Alternatively throw a RangeError when the calculations exceed these limits.

```
function baseRandom(min, max) {
      return min + nativeFloor(nativeRandom() * (max - min + 1));
}
```

A reference: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28461796/randomint-function-that-can-uniformly-handle-the-full-range-of-min-and-max-safe

Would it be possible to modify the underlying matching function behind _.where and similar functions to allow matching on arrays of values in addition to the standard simple key:value matching? I understand this might add too much of a performance hit, but I feel like this would be a pretty useful addition.

**Example:**

``` JavaScript
var arr = [{val: 1}, {val: 2}, {val: 3}];

var filter = {val: [1, 3]};

_.where(arr, filter);
// Ideally would return => [{val: 1}, {val: 3}]
```

The matching function could potentially look something like this:

``` JavaScript
function isMatch(obj, filter) {
  for (var prop in filter) {
    if (filter.hasOwnProperty(prop)) {
      if (_.isArray(filter[prop])) {
        if (filter[prop].indexOf(obj[prop]) === -1) return false;
      }
      else {
        if (obj[prop] !== filter[prop]) return false;
      }
    }
  }

  return true;
}
```

